item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Stephen Colbert
item.description: "Equations are the devil's sentences." -- Stephen Colbert

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "I am a cage, in search of a bird." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Kafka, Franz
item.description: "I am in chains. Don't touch my chains." -- Kafka, Franz

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "There is an infinite amount of hope in the universe ... but not for us." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "In man's struggle against the world, bet on the world." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "I do not speak as I think, I do not think as I should, and so it all goes on in helpless darkness." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "My peers, lately, have found companionship through means of intoxication--it makes them sociable. I, however, cannot force myself to use drugs to cheat on my loneliness--it is all that I have--and when the drugs and alcohol dissipate, will be all that my peers have as well." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "I need solitude for my writing; not 'like a hermit' - that wouldn't be enough - but like a dead man." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "God gives the nuts, but he does not crack them." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "You are free and that is why you are lost." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "I usually solve problems by letting them devour me." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "What do I have in common with Jews? I don't even have anything in common with myself. " -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "Faith, like a guillotine. As heavy, as light." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "There is a destination but no way there; what we refer to as way is hesitation." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "You see, I have only such a fugitive awareness of things around me that I always feel they were once real and are now fleeting away." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "I lack nothing. I only needed myself." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Haruki Murakami
item.description: "If you only read the books that everyone else is reading, you can only think what everyone else is thinking." -- Haruki Murakami

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by haruki murakami
item.description: "Pain is inevitable. Suffering is optional." -- haruki murakami

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Haruki Murakami
item.description: "Nobody likes being alone that much. I don't go out of my way to make friends, that's all. It just leads to disappointment. " -- Haruki Murakami

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Haruki Murakami
item.description: "That's what the world is , after all: an endless battle of contrasting memories." -- Haruki Murakami

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Zadie Smith
item.description: "This is what divorce is: taking things you no longer want from people you no longer love." -- Zadie Smith

item.title: Sabrina add a quote by Zadie Smith
item.description: "Every moment happens twice: inside and outside, and they are two different histories." -- Zadie Smith
